result.execSummary:
The defendant Ulanda M Green was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft from Person or Corpse [Modifiers: Penalty - Theft if Taken/Person/Corpse, Penalties for Felonies-Class "G" Felony], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Original PLEA & SENTENCING Transcript (34 pages) commencing 07/27/2015 received and filed. DA

Statements by state, defense counsel and defendant.

As to Count 2 as added on the amended information:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  3 YEARS consecutive to any other sentence; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR and 6 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR and 6 MONTHS. 

Court finds defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program and the Substance Abuse program. 
 
Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 2 YEARS and 6 MONTHS probation.  

Court recommends that the defendant should be supervised by the mental health division.


 Conditions of Probation/ Extended Supervision if revoked:
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- Absolute/maintain sobriety, no alcohol, no drugs.
- No possession/consumption/selling/distribution of illegal drugs/alcohol.
- Random urine screens as deemed appropriate.
- Provide a DNA sample.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Department to determine an appropriate payment plan:
Restitution in the amount of $39.99 payable to Hyun O. H.; 
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA and any victim surcharge); 
All applicable fees of supervision.
-  If revoked, the Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.



Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he/she may never possess a firearm. 
Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.
Court advised defendant that he/she may not vote until his/her civil rights have been restored.  

Filed:  
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence 
Victim Impact Statement    
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement

Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered Count 1 dismissed and read-in to case for the purposes of sentencing.

As to Count 2 as added to the Amended Information:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

Defendant Ulanda M Green in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Defendant Ulanda M Green in custody.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Filed, original amended information; copy served on defendant.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of information, waives formal reading, pleads not guilty.  
Court ordered Cournt 2 added to the Information- Theft from Person or Corpse, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.20(1)(a), 943.20(1)(a) and 939.50(3)(g), a Class G Felony.

Attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter in court, defendant Ulanda M Green not in court, in custody.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for scheduling conference.  Defense requests plea and sentencing date.  Case remains calendared in Branch 22.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for July 27, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Original PRELIMINARY HEARING Transcript (13 pages) commencing May 4, 2015 received and filed.
Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.

Defendant Ulanda M Green in court with attorney Catelin Firer for Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Defendant Ulanda M Green in custody.  Ronald Dague for Patrick Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the state:Kenyatte Wooden-MPD Detective.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and pleads not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 22.  Scheduling conference scheduled for May 19, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for 05-04-2015 at 01:30 pm.

As an additional condition of bail:

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for supervision with the Pretrial Electronic Monitoring Program.  Drug Testing.  Release for legal appointments

No weapons

Defendant Ulanda M Green in court with attorney Anne M Jaspers.  Defendant Ulanda M Green in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant has a lower number case pending in Branch 22.

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Witkowiak, Branch 22.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.
